    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Here are the docs for the flag. You can check with `lighthouse bn --help`\r\n```\r\n        --trusted-peers <TRUSTED_PEERS>\r\n            One or more comma-delimited trusted peer ids which always have the highest score according to the peer\r\n            scoring system.\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote that Lighthouse will not connect to this peer_id given the flag. Just that it will not remove it from it's peer list once connected. You can connect to it by passing it in the `--libp2p-addresses` flag\r\n\r\n```\r\n        --libp2p-addresses <MULTIADDR>\r\n            One or more comma-delimited multiaddrs to manually connect to a libp2p peer without an ENR.\r\n```\r\nThe multiaddr format is `/ip4/<IP-ADDR>/tcp/<PORT>`",
